---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro'
import QuoteForm from '@/components/QuoteForm'
import TrustBar from '@/components/TrustBar.astro'

const title = "Gutter Repairs Uxbridge UB8 | Same-Week Response"
const description = "Fast gutter repairs in Uxbridge UB8. Leaking joints, sagging gutters, cracked sections. Specialists in 1930s semi-detached and Victorian terraces."
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-white">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div class="relative h-96 overflow-hidden">
      <img src="/images/gutter-repairs-hero.jpg" alt="Gutter repairs in Uxbridge" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/40"></div>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center">
        <div class="text-center text-white">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Gutter Repairs Uxbridge</h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl">Fast response, expert repairs, no water damage</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <nav class="bg-gray-100 px-4 py-3">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
          <li><a href="/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Home</a></li>
          <li class="text-gray-500">/</li>
          <li><a href="/locations" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Locations</a></li>
          <li class="text-gray-500">/</li>
          <li><a href="/locations/uxbridge" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Uxbridge</a></li>
          <li class="text-gray-500">/</li>
          <li class="text-gray-700">Gutter Repairs</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <!-- Quick Answer Box -->
      <div class="quick-answer bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mb-12 rounded">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Quick Answer</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We repair leaking joints, sagging gutters, cracked sections and loose brackets in Uxbridge UB8. Most repairs take 1 to 2 hours and are completed in a single visit. We aim to respond within 48 hours for urgent issues.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-2">
          <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Expert Gutter Repairs for Uxbridge Properties</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Uxbridge's historic 1930s semi-detached and Victorian terraces are beautiful properties, but their older guttering systems often develop leaks, sag under weight, or suffer joint deterioration. Water leaks can cause serious damage to fascia boards, soffits, and external walls if not addressed quickly.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Our specialist gutter repair service in Uxbridge UB8 identifies and fixes problems before they become expensive. Whether your gutter is leaking at the joints, sagging due to debris weight, or cracked from age, we provide same-day or next-day response on urgent jobs.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Common Gutter Problems We Fix in Uxbridge</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-orange-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Leaking Joints and Seals</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Metal gutters on 1930s semi-detached and Victorian terraces in Uxbridge suffer from joint corrosion and seal failure. We re-seal or replace sections to stop water overflow.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-orange-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Sagging Gutters</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">When debris accumulates and gutters pull away from fascia boards, water pools and overflows. We reinstall brackets, tighten fixings, and restore proper drainage slope.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-orange-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Cracked and Split Sections</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Age, frost damage, or impact can crack gutters. We patch minor cracks or replace affected sections to prevent water ingress on your Uxbridge home.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-orange-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Loose or Missing Brackets</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Brackets hold gutters securely to fascia. We tighten loose fixings, replace corroded brackets, and ensure gutters are properly supported across your UB8 property.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-orange-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Blocked Downpipes</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Debris or ice buildup can block downpipes, causing water to back up and overflow from gutters. We clear blockages and ensure free drainage.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-orange-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Rust and Corrosion</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Metal gutters on older Uxbridge properties develop rust spots. We treat corrosion, apply protective coatings, or replace damaged sections.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Our Repair Process for Uxbridge UB8 Homes</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-blue-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Step 1: Rapid Assessment</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">We inspect your Uxbridge gutters to identify the source of leaks, damage, or sagging. Photographs are taken to document the issue before repair.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-blue-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Step 2: Repair Quote</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">We provide a clear quote for the repair work needed, explaining whether the gutter can be saved or needs replacement. No hidden charges.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-blue-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Step 3: Professional Repair</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">Our team completes the repair using quality materials suited to your 1930s semi-detached or Victorian terraces property in Uxbridge.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded border-l-4 border-blue-500">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Step 4: Testing and Report</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">We test gutters and downpipes with water to confirm the repair is successful, then provide a written report for your records.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Gutter Repair Pricing in Uxbridge</h3>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
              <table class="w-full border-collapse">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="bg-blue-100">
                    <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left font-semibold">Repair Type</th>
                    <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left font-semibold">Typical Price</th>
                    <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left font-semibold">Time</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Re-seal leaking joint</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">£40–£80</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">30–45 mins</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Replace gutter section (up to 2 metres)</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">£80–£150</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">60–90 mins</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Tighten/replace brackets (2–4 brackets)</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">£50–£100</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">45–60 mins</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Clear downpipe blockage</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">£40–£80</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">30–45 mins</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Rust treatment and sealant</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">£60–£120</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">45–60 mins</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Replace full 1930s semi-detached gutter run</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">£300–£600</td>
                    <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">4–6 hours</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-4">*Prices vary based on gutter type, run length, and repair complexity. Call for a free quote on your Uxbridge UB8 property.</p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Repair vs Replacement: What Your Uxbridge Home Needs</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Not every gutter problem requires full replacement. We help Uxbridge property owners decide whether repair or replacement is the right choice.
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="border-2 border-green-300 bg-green-50 p-4 rounded">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 text-lg">Repair is Right When:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm">
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-green-600">✓</span>
                    <span>Problem is isolated to one section</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-green-600">✓</span>
                    <span>Gutters are less than 20 years old</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-green-600">✓</span>
                    <span>Material is in good condition elsewhere</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-green-600">✓</span>
                    <span>Repair cost is under 50% of replacement</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-green-600">✓</span>
                    <span>You want to keep original materials on 1930s semi-detached or Victorian properties</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="border-2 border-red-300 bg-red-50 p-4 rounded">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 text-lg">Replace When:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm">
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-red-600">✗</span>
                    <span>Multiple sections are damaged or leaking</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-red-600">✗</span>
                    <span>Extensive rust or corrosion throughout</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-red-600">✗</span>
                    <span>Gutters are over 30 years old</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-red-600">✗</span>
                    <span>Frequent repairs needed in past 2 years</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="text-red-600">✗</span>
                    <span>Fascia or soffit requires replacement</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Why 1930s Semi-Detached and Victorian Terraces in Uxbridge Develop Gutter Problems</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Uxbridge's historic housing stock includes many 1930s semi-detached homes and Victorian terraces, and these properties share common gutter issues:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">1930s Semi-Detached:</span>
                <span>Deep roof lines and complex guttering systems collect debris from mature trees. Metal gutters often develop joint leaks and rust spots from decades of exposure. Concrete-based downpipes can crack and block easily.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">Victorian Terraces:</span>
                <span>Ornate cast iron gutters are prone to corrosion, and their decorative edges trap leaves and moss. Joints can weep if seals fail. Three-storey height makes repairs more hazardous and expensive.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">General Issues:</span>
                <span>Uxbridge's leafy streets mean gutters fill quickly, putting extra weight on aging brackets. Temperature fluctuations between seasons cause expansion and contraction, weakening seals and fixings.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <!-- Related Services in Uxbridge -->
          <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Related Services in Uxbridge UB8</h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <a href="/locations/uxbridge/gutter-cleaning" class="block p-4 border-2 border-blue-200 rounded hover:border-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-50 transition">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Gutter Cleaning</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Prevent damage with regular cleaning and debris removal</p>
              </a>
              <a href="/locations/uxbridge/gutter-replacement" class="block p-4 border-2 border-blue-200 rounded hover:border-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-50 transition">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Gutter Replacement</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Full replacement with uPVC or cast iron systems</p>
              </a>
              <a href="/locations/uxbridge/fascia-soffit-cleaning" class="block p-4 border-2 border-blue-200 rounded hover:border-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-50 transition">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Fascia & Soffit Cleaning</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Clean and protect your fascia boards from damage</p>
              </a>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- FAQ Section with Schema -->
          <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-gray-50 px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-100">
                  Q1: How much do gutter repairs cost in Uxbridge?
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white border-t border-gray-300">
                  <p class="text-gray-700">Repair costs in Uxbridge range from £40–£150 for minor fixes like re-sealing joints or replacing brackets, to £300–£600 for larger repairs on full gutter runs. We provide a free quote after inspecting your UB8 property.</p>
                </div>
              </details>

              <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-gray-50 px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-100">
                  Q2: Can you repair cast iron gutters in UB8?
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white border-t border-gray-300">
                  <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, we specialise in repairing cast iron gutters on Victorian terraces throughout Uxbridge. We can re-seal joints, treat rust, and replace damaged sections while preserving the original character of your UB8 property.</p>
                </div>
              </details>

              <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-gray-50 px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-100">
                  Q3: My gutter is leaking at the joint in Uxbridge - can you fix it same day?
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white border-t border-gray-300">
                  <p class="text-gray-700">We aim to respond to urgent gutter repairs in Uxbridge within 48 hours. Depending on availability and the complexity of the joint leak, same-day repair may be possible. Contact us immediately to check if your UB8 property can be prioritised.</p>
                </div>
              </details>

              <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-gray-50 px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-100">
                  Q4: What causes gutters to sag on 1930s semi-detached and Victorian terraces in Uxbridge?
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white border-t border-gray-300">
                  <p class="text-gray-700">Sagging gutters on 1930s semi-detached and Victorian terraces in Uxbridge are usually caused by: debris weight (especially from mature trees), corroded or loose brackets, and age-related deterioration. We reinstall brackets and restore proper pitch to prevent water pooling.</p>
                </div>
              </details>

              <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-gray-50 px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-100">
                  Q5: How do I know if my Uxbridge home needs repairs or a full replacement?
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white border-t border-gray-300">
                  <p class="text-gray-700">If the problem is limited to one or two sections and gutters are under 20 years old, repair is usually best. If you have multiple leaks, widespread rust, or frequent damage, replacement is more cost-effective. We'll advise on your Uxbridge UB8 property during inspection.</p>
                </div>
              </details>

              <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-gray-50 px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-100">
                  Q6: Do you repair fascia boards as well as gutters in UB8?
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white border-t border-gray-300">
                  <p class="text-gray-700">We repair gutters primarily, but we can identify fascia damage caused by water leaks and recommend replacement options. Many gutter repairs in Uxbridge involve checking fascia condition to prevent future problems on your 1930s semi-detached or Victorian terraces.</p>
                </div>
              </details>

              <details class="border border-gray-300 rounded overflow-hidden">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer bg-gray-50 px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-100">
                  Q7: Are your gutter repairs guaranteed in Uxbridge?
                </summary>
                <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white border-t border-gray-300">
                  <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, all gutter repairs completed in Uxbridge include a workmanship guarantee. If the same problem recurs within 12 months, we'll return to fix it at no additional cost. We stand behind every repair on your UB8 property.</p>
                </div>
              </details>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Related Services in Other Areas -->
          <section class="mb-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Gutter Repairs in Nearby Areas</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">We also provide gutter repair services to neighbouring towns:</p>
            <div class="space-y-2">
